#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Procedure of raw images deployment"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "&productname; provides raw images that can be directly deployed to your device storage&mdash;a memory card, USB flash drive, or a hard disk. The options for which type of device you can deploy the image to depend on your particular hardware&mdash;follow your vendor documentation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "To initially configure the deployed image, you need to prepare the configuration data as described in <xref linkend=\"pro-preparing-configuration-device\"/> and you need to copy the configuration data to a device (e.g. USB disk). The device needs to be connected to your host running &slema; during its first boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "To prepare the setup, you will need two separate devices. One for the raw disk image, where &slema; will run, and another one that serves as a configuration media."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the raw disk image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "Download the raw image and decompress it:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;xz -d &lt;downloaded_image.raw.xz&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy the decompressed image to the device where &slema; will run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;dd if=&lt;downloaded_image.raw&gt; of=/dev/sdX"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following procedure describes how to prepare the configuration device (usually a USB flash disk)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preparing the configuration device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "Format the disk to any file system supported by &slema;: FAT, Ext4, etc.:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      "&prompt.user;sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdY\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:59
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the device label to either <literal>ignition</literal> or <literal>combustion</literal> . For the Ext4 file system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;sudo e2label /dev/sdY ignition"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use any type of configuration storage media that your virtualization system or your hardware supports&mdash;ISO image, a USB flash disk, etc."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount the device:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      "&prompt.user;sudo mount /dev/sdY /mnt\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create the directory structure as mentioned in <xref linkend=\"cha-images-ignition\"/> or <xref linkend=\"cha-images-combustion\"/> , depending on the configuration tool used:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      "&prompt.user;sudo mkdir -p /mnt/ignition/\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "or:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      "&prompt.user;sudo mkdir -p /mnt/combustion/\n"
      ""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prior to booting for the first time, prepare all elements of the configuration that will be used by <xref linkend=\"cha-images-ignition\" xrefstyle=\"template:Ignition\"/> or <xref linkend=\"cha-images-combustion\" xrefstyle=\"template:Combustion\"/> . The minimal configuration must provide a password for &rootuser;, otherwise the system will not be accessible after the first boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the first boot, you need to register your &slem; instance by using the command line tool <command>SUSEConnect</command> . For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-images-registration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; has available enxtension for live patching. To use this extension, you need to add the extension to your subscirption from the installed system. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-adding-extension\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Registration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Registering the system is possible from the command line using <command>SUSEConnect</command> . For information that goes beyond the scope of this section, refer to the inline documentation with <command>SUSEConnect --help</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Product registration with SUSEConnect"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "To register &productname; with &scc;, run <command>SUSEConnect</command> as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;SUSEConnect -r <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable> -e <replaceable>EMAIL_ADDRESS</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "To register with a local registration server, additionally provide the URL to the server:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;SUSEConnect -r <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable> -e <replaceable>EMAIL_ADDRESS</replaceable> \\\n"
      "--url \"https://suse_register.&exampledomain;/\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Replace <replaceable>REGISTRATION_CODE</replaceable> with the registration code you received with your copy of &productname;. Replace <replaceable>EMAIL_ADDRESS</replaceable> with the e-mail address associated with the &suse; account you or your organization uses to manage subscriptions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "&productname; is now registered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding extension"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case you need to activate the live patching extension, list available extensions by running at first:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      " &prompt.root;transactional-update --quiet register -list-extensions\n"
      " "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "The output provides you with a command how to activate the live patching extension:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      " &prompt.root;transactional-update register -p sle-module-live-patching/15.3/x86_64 -r <replaceable>registration code</replaceable>\n"
      " "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "To deactivate the extension, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "\n"
      " &prompt.root;transactional-update register -d -p sle-module-live-patching/15.3/x86_64\n"
      " "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rebooting after activating/deactivating extensions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_procedure.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid "As the extension activation or deactivation is performed as a transactional-update and thus creates a new snapshot, you need to restart your system to boot to the new snapshot and apply the changes."
msgstr ""

